{"info": {"author": "Clemens-Alexander Brust", "author_email": "cabrust@pm.me", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "# Bosch Smart Home Local API Python Library\n\nThis library implements the local communication REST API for the Bosch Smart Home system.\nThe API documentation is available [here](https://github.com/BoschSmartHome/bosch-shc-api-docs).\nIt supports both long and short polling. The following device services are implemented:\n * ```TemperatureLevel```\n * ```ValveTappet```\n * ```ShutterContact```\n * ```RoomClimateControl```\n\nExample:\n```python\nimport bshlocal\n\n# Create session\nsession = bshlocal.BSHLocalSession(controller_ip=\"192.168.25.51\", certificate='cert.pem', key='key.pem')\ndevice = session.device('roomClimateControl_hz_5')\nservice = device.device_service('TemperatureLevel')\nprint(service.temperature)\n\n# Update this service's state\nservice.short_poll()\n\n# Start long polling thread in background\nsession.start_polling()\n\n# Do work here\n...\n\n# Stop polling\nsession.stop_polling()\n```\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/cabrust/bshlocal", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "bshlocal", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/bshlocal/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/bshlocal/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/cabrust/bshlocal"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/bshlocal/0.0.7/", "requires_dist": ["requests (==2.22)"], "requires_python": ">=3.7", "summary": "Bosch Smart Home Local API Python Library", "version": "0.0.7", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Bosch Smart Home Local API Python Library</h1>\n<p>This library implements the local communication REST API for the Bosch Smart Home system.\nThe API documentation is available <a href=\"https://github.com/BoschSmartHome/bosch-shc-api-docs\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>.\nIt supports both long and short polling. The following device services are implemented:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>TemperatureLevel</code></li>\n<li><code>ValveTappet</code></li>\n<li><code>ShutterContact</code></li>\n<li><code>RoomClimateControl</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">bshlocal</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Create session</span>\n<span class=\"n\">session</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">bshlocal</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">BSHLocalSession</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">controller_ip</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">\"192.168.25.51\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">certificate</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s1\">'cert.pem'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">key</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s1\">'key.pem'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">device</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">session</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">device</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'roomClimateControl_hz_5'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">service</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">device</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">device_service</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'TemperatureLevel'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">print</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">service</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">temperature</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Update this service's state</span>\n<span class=\"n\">service</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">short_poll</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Start long polling thread in background</span>\n<span class=\"n\">session</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">start_polling</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Do work here</span>\n<span class=\"o\">...</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Stop polling</span>\n<span class=\"n\">session</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">stop_polling</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6410146, "releases": {"0.0.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "0e687a43417ed82ba173acfdfbb0173c", "sha256": "4996c368a9971e2394385a48d959aeb12641d59eaf8bd4bfa3abb061ea82bef6"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "bshlocal-0.0.2-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "0e687a43417ed82ba173acfdfbb0173c", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.7", "size": 8621, "upload_time": "2020-01-05T16:38:39", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-01-05T16:38:39.681573Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/70/2a/acfa51529d5e65239476657081583698583c54bdec11838ad84da57ad82f/bshlocal-0.0.2-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "5dd18e1cfb72bbdbb2931f5a3a0fb735", "sha256": "1c8d4e037513a5df2b07d27028c5201337a99df57e7362f2092f2d42f3593a89"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "bshlocal-0.0.2.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "5dd18e1cfb72bbdbb2931f5a3a0fb735", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.7", "size": 5548, "upload_time": "2020-01-05T16:38:41", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-01-05T16:38:41.975212Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/86/c1/8840d1c5bc766272e9d62a92894e691bb88b51f152178ce8d22fafc4a43e/bshlocal-0.0.2.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.3": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "3a878b1f2b7a366a6effe58461249c5b", "sha256": "332608eb0a88087c53dd60478d0d2b6d1719cf606912fcdd2d52543113460759